'We'll Get Through This,' Pence Tells Air Force Academy GraduatesEnlarge this image toggle caption David Zalubowski/AP David Zalubowski/APThey still threw their caps into the air as F-16s flew overhead.
But this year's graduation of the U.S. Air Force Academy near Colorado Springs was different from any other in the institution's history.
"We gather at a time of national crisis as the coronavirus epidemic impacts our nation and the wider world," Pence said.
He cited medical workers on the front lines, farmers and grocers keeping America fed, and autoworkers who are making medical equipment to save lives.
Eighty-six cadets will join the Space Force.